  "summary": "klaudius ships Telegram-based exfiltration channel",
  "details": "The package's bundled output (dist/chunk-SZ4KCTSL.js line 6 and dist/bin.js line 11) contains hardcoded calls to https://api.telegram.org with POST requests via fetch(). Telegram's bot API is a well-documented attacker C2 channel used to relay collected data out of installer environments without requiring attacker-controlled domain infrastructure. The presence of a hardcoded api.telegram.org POST inside a CLI bin script (dist/bin.js) indicates the bot endpoint is invoked when the tool runs, not as a configurable user feature. Combined with a chunked/bundled distribution that hides the call site, this matches the hardcoded-C2-exfiltration fingerprint.",
